<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_45541401" data-cid="45541401">
    <div id="comment_45541401">
        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Insightful">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:price"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:price<span> (4, Insightful)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~Chris+Mattern" class="author" title="author name and user ID">Chris Mattern (191822) </a> | about 10 months ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=4493645&cid=45541401">(#45541401)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_45541401" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Insightful">
            <div class="comment-body"><blockquote><div><p>The per-unit cost of printing a book and shipping it in bulk to a distributer is a trivial portion of the price of a book.</p></div></blockquote><p>I found <a href="http://ireaderreview.com/2009/05/03/book-cost-analysis-cost-of-physical-book-publishing/" title="ireaderreview.com">one breakdown of printed book cost analysis analysis</a> <span class="domain-text"> [ireaderreview.com]</span>  that put printing and distribution at 20% of a book's cover price, and retailer's markup at 40%.  A lot of that retailer's markup is inventory cost--what it costs the retailer to store and display copies of the book.  Even though the actual *printing* cost is only 10% of the book's price, you then have to pay for dealing with the physical form and getting it to the customer, which is much tougher than getting a computer file to the customer.  At a guess, I'd say that 30% to 40% of the cost of a physical book is tied to paying for its physical aspects.  Not so trivial.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_45541401">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="4493645" data-cid="45541401">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="45541401" data-pid="45541401" data-cid="45541401"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default show-parent" href=""><i class="fa fa-level-up"></i> Parent</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default menu-trigger moderatebtn"><i class="fa fa-gavel"></i> Moderate
                    
