        <div id="comment_body_45541779" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>Although I do not fit in this demographic and now do the majority of my reading on my Kindle, I, too, prefer printed books.  There are plenty of good things about ebooks.  I particularly like the portability and built in dictionary.  In spite of the conveniences that ebooks offer, I still prefer the FEEL of a real printed book.  As a result, I have a good collection on my Kindle and an overloaded bookshelf.</p></div>
